From 317c4388214210263e29581d015b4dfcf8907255 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 23:29:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman_pcd: v1.1-A install-now-for-existing-ports
 (late-registration replay)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Empirical M2 acceptance-gate verification on 2026-05-24 (kernel
6.18.31-vyos) revealed that ask_init()'s fs_initcall completes AFTER
fman_port_init() for all five LS1046A MAC ports despite ask being
built-in. Root cause: async/parallel platform-bus probe plus the
MODULE_SIG_FORCE startup cost stall ask_init past every fman_port
probe, so by the time ask calls fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook()
the hook table is updated but the hook itself never fires for the
already-initialised ports. Result: throughput 6.861 Gbps with
kernel-net CPU 33.14 %% (M2 gate is ≤ 5 %%).

This patch lands option (c) from the failure analysis -- retroactive
replay -- preserving ask.ko's OOT property without forcing the hook
registration earlier in the boot sequence:

  - Add pcd->pending_ports list and struct fman_pcd_pending_port to
    fman_pcd.c so each -ENOENT fall-through in fman_port_init() can
    record (port_id, default_base_fqid, default_hash_size).

  - fman_pcd_record_pending_port() (NOT exported, same TU as
    fman_port.c) appends one record per untouched port. Failure is
    non-fatal; the port simply will not be retroactively re-claimed.

  - fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() (EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL)
    drains the queue by splicing it onto a local list (so the hook
    can sleep / call back into PCD APIs without recursive lock),
    invoking the registered hook for each captured port, removing
    claimed entries (rc == 0), splicing declined ones (-ENOENT)
    back, and dropping fatal entries to prevent retry loops.
    Returns the first fatal errno or 0 on success.

  - fman_port.c -ENOENT branch now calls
    fman_pcd_record_pending_port() before falling through to
    mainline keygen_port_hashing_init(). Warn-and-continue on
    record failure -- mainline RSS still applies.

  - ask_hw.c immediately after fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook()
    calls fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports(). Errors are
    non-fatal -- the kernel still forwards via mainline RSS for
    any port the replay could not claim.

  - fman_pcd_release() drains any unclaimed pending_port records
    on subsystem teardown.

Acceptance signature: 'dmesg | grep fman_pcd' shows
'install_now: claimed=N declined=M failed=K' with N matching the
count of FMan RX ports ask is configured to own; bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py
shows non-zero kgse_ccbs on claimed schemes; M2 acceptance gate
expected to flip throughput 6.861 -> >=7 Gbps and kernel-net CPU
33.14 %% -> < 5 %%.
---
 .../net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c    | 222 ++++++++++++++++--
 .../freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h        |  19 +-
 .../net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c   |  36 ++-
 include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h                  |  37 ++-
 4 files changed, 284 insertions(+), 30 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
index 49d675f..128a94e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
@@ -114,24 +114,61 @@ struct fman_pcd {
 	struct list_head cc_trees;
 	struct list_head manip_profiles;
 	struct list_head plcr_profiles;
-	struct list_head replic_groups;
+struct list_head replic_groups;
 
-	struct dentry *debugfs_dir;
+struct dentry *debugfs_dir;
 
-	/*
-	 * PR14z19 Path A: optional pre-netdev hook. When set, fman_port_init()
-	 * calls this hook in lieu of the default keygen_port_hashing_init()
-	 * for ports where the hook returns 0 (== "I own this port, skip
-	 * default RSS"). Returning -ENOENT means "not my port, fall through".
-	 * Any other negative value is treated as a fatal probe error.
-	 *
-	 * Single hook per FMan instance. Registered before dpaa_eth_probe()
-	 * runs (ask.ko is built-in via Kconfig bool, so its module_init runs
-	 * during fs_initcall before the dpaa_eth probe). pcd->lock protects
-	 * the install/uninstall; the hook itself is invoked outside the lock.
-	 */
-	fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t pre_netdev_hook;
-	void *pre_netdev_hook_priv;
+/*
+ * PR14z19 Path A: optional pre-netdev hook. When set, fman_port_init()
+ * calls this hook in lieu of the default keygen_port_hashing_init()
+ * for ports where the hook returns 0 (== "I own this port, skip
+ * default RSS"). Returning -ENOENT means "not my port, fall through".
+ * Any other negative value is treated as a fatal probe error.
+ *
+ * Single hook per FMan instance. Registered before dpaa_eth_probe()
+ * runs (ask.ko is built-in via Kconfig bool, so its module_init runs
+ * during fs_initcall before the dpaa_eth probe). pcd->lock protects
+ * the install/uninstall; the hook itself is invoked outside the lock.
+ */
+fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t pre_netdev_hook;
+void *pre_netdev_hook_priv;
+
+/*
+ * v1.1-A late-registration replay queue.
+ *
+ * Even though ask is built-in and ask_init() runs at fs_initcall,
+ * empirical M2 verification (2026-05-24) showed that fman_port_init()
+ * for all five MACs frequently completes BEFORE the hook is
+ * registered: the FMan platform driver's probe schedules port probes
+ * during device_initcall, and on parallel/async probe paths some of
+ * those probes can race ahead of ask's hook registration --
+ * especially when MODULE_SIG_FORCE verification stalls ask_init.
+ *
+ * Solution: whenever fman_port_init() falls through to mainline
+ * keygen_port_hashing_init() (i.e. invoke_pre_netdev_hook returned
+ * -ENOENT because no hook was yet installed), we record the port's
+ * (port_id, default_base_fqid, default_hash_size) tuple on this
+ * list. Later, when ask finally calls
+ * fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook(), it ALSO calls
+ * fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() which drains this list
+ * by invoking the freshly-registered hook for each captured port.
+ *
+ * Each successfully-claimed port (hook returns 0) is removed from
+ * the list; -ENOENT or fatal errors leave the entry in place (or
+ * are propagated to the caller, respectively).
+ *
+ * Locking: pcd->lock protects the list during append/drain. The
+ * hook callback runs OUTSIDE the lock so it may sleep and call back
+ * into PCD APIs.
+ */
+struct list_head pending_ports;
+};
+
+struct fman_pcd_pending_port {
+struct list_head node;
+u8 hwport_id;
+u32 default_base_fqid;
+u32 default_hash_size;
 };
 
 /*
@@ -319,6 +356,141 @@ int fman_pcd_invoke_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hwport_id,
 		    default_hash_size, priv);
 }
 
+/*
+ * v1.1-A: fman_pcd_record_pending_port() - same-module helper consumed
+ * by fman_port.c whenever fman_port_init() falls through to the
+ * mainline keygen_port_hashing_init() path because no pre-netdev hook
+ * was registered at that moment. We capture
+ * (port_id, base_fqid, hash_size) so a later
+ * fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() call from ask can replay
+ * the hook for ports that probed before ask_init() ran.
+ *
+ * Failures are non-fatal: a -ENOMEM means this particular port will
+ * not be retroactively re-claimed. The caller logs and continues.
+ *
+ * Locking: callable from process context. kzalloc(GFP_KERNEL) is
+ * outside pcd->lock; the list append is inside.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_record_pending_port(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hwport_id,
+				 u32 default_base_fqid,
+				 u32 default_hash_size)
+{
+	struct fman_pcd_pending_port *p;
+
+	if (!pcd)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	p = kzalloc(sizeof(*p), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!p)
+		return -ENOMEM;
+
+	p->hwport_id = hwport_id;
+	p->default_base_fqid = default_base_fqid;
+	p->default_hash_size = default_hash_size;
+	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&p->node);
+
+	mutex_lock(&pcd->lock);
+	list_add_tail(&p->node, &pcd->pending_ports);
+	mutex_unlock(&pcd->lock);
+
+	return 0;
+}
+
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() - retroactively invoke
+ * the registered pre-netdev hook for every fman_port that completed
+ * fman_port_init() BEFORE the hook was installed.
+ * @pcd: PCD handle.
+ *
+ * Background: even though ask is built-in and its fs_initcall runs
+ * before dpaa_eth's device_initcall, parallel/async platform probing
+ * means individual fman_port platform devices can probe ahead of
+ * ask_init(). Empirical M2 verification on 2026-05-24 (kernel
+ * 6.18.31-vyos) confirmed all five MAC ports had completed init
+ * before the hook was registered: the hook never fired, every
+ * ask_hw_flow_insert_v4_tcp() returned -ENODEV, throughput was
+ * 6.861 Gbps but kernel-net CPU stayed at 33.14 %% because forwarding
+ * was running in the SW path.
+ *
+ * This function drains pcd->pending_ports, invoking the hook for
+ * each captured port. Successfully-claimed ports (hook returns 0)
+ * are removed. -ENOENT entries remain queued (defensive: should not
+ * occur since the caller registered the hook moments earlier).
+ * Fatal errors are propagated; the failing entry is dropped to avoid
+ * retry loops.
+ *
+ * The hook is invoked OUTSIDE pcd->lock so it may sleep and call
+ * back into PCD APIs (e.g. KG-scheme attach via the graft pathway).
+ *
+ * Acceptance signature: after the call, dmesg should show
+ * "ask: pcd install: schemes 3+4 claimed" (or whichever schemes the
+ * ASK install hook selects), and bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py should show
+ * non-zero kgse_ccbs on the claimed schemes.
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success (including the empty-list case). Negative
+ * errno if any hook invocation returned a fatal error; the caller
+ * may choose to ignore (ports remain on the default RSS scheme).
+ * -EINVAL if pcd is NULL; -ENOENT if no hook is currently registered.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports(struct fman_pcd *pcd)
+{
+	fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t hook;
+	void *priv;
+	struct fman_pcd_pending_port *p, *tmp;
+	LIST_HEAD(snapshot);
+	int rc, first_err = 0;
+	unsigned int claimed = 0, declined = 0, failed = 0;
+
+	if (!pcd)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	mutex_lock(&pcd->lock);
+	hook = pcd->pre_netdev_hook;
+	priv = pcd->pre_netdev_hook_priv;
+	if (!hook) {
+		mutex_unlock(&pcd->lock);
+		return -ENOENT;
+	}
+	/*
+	 * Splice pending_ports onto a local list so we can invoke the
+	 * hook outside pcd->lock (the hook may call back into PCD APIs
+	 * which take the same lock). Entries that remain unclaimed are
+	 * spliced back at the end.
+	 */
+	list_splice_init(&pcd->pending_ports, &snapshot);
+	mutex_unlock(&pcd->lock);
+
+	list_for_each_entry_safe(p, tmp, &snapshot, node) {
+		rc = hook(pcd, p->hwport_id, p->default_base_fqid,
+			  p->default_hash_size, priv);
+		if (rc == 0) {
+			list_del(&p->node);
+			kfree(p);
+			claimed++;
+		} else if (rc == -ENOENT) {
+			declined++;
+			/* leave on snapshot list -> spliced back below */
+		} else {
+			list_del(&p->node);
+			kfree(p);
+			failed++;
+			if (!first_err)
+				first_err = rc;
+		}
+	}
+
+	/* Splice any unclaimed (declined) entries back to pending_ports. */
+	mutex_lock(&pcd->lock);
+	list_splice(&snapshot, &pcd->pending_ports);
+	mutex_unlock(&pcd->lock);
+
+	dev_info(fman_get_dev(pcd->fman),
+		 "fman_pcd: install_now: claimed=%u declined=%u failed=%u\n",
+		 claimed, declined, failed);
+
+	return first_err;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports);
 
 /**
  * fman_pcd_init() - initialise the PCD subsystem for an FMan instance.
@@ -424,9 +596,23 @@ void fman_pcd_release(struct fman_pcd *pcd)
 	WARN_ON(!list_empty(&pcd->cc_trees));
 	WARN_ON(!list_empty(&pcd->manip_profiles));
 	WARN_ON(!list_empty(&pcd->plcr_profiles));
-	WARN_ON(!list_empty(&pcd->replic_groups));
+WARN_ON(!list_empty(&pcd->replic_groups));
+
+/*
+ * v1.1-A: drain any pending_ports entries that were never claimed.
+ * Non-fatal: their default RSS scheme is already programmed; the
+ * leak here would only be the small kzalloc'd record.
+ */
+{
+struct fman_pcd_pending_port *p, *tmp;
+
+list_for_each_entry_safe(p, tmp, &pcd->pending_ports, node) {
+list_del(&p->node);
+kfree(p);
+}
+}
 
-	if (!IS_ERR_VALUE(pcd->muram_offset))
+if (!IS_ERR_VALUE(pcd->muram_offset))
 		fman_muram_free_mem(fman_get_muram(pcd->fman),
 				    pcd->muram_offset,
 				    pcd->muram_reserved);
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h
index ef88eca..be5e9dd 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_internal.h
@@ -117,7 +117,22 @@ unsigned long fman_pcd_replic_group_source_td_off(
  *   public register/unregister surface is in <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>.
  */
 int fman_pcd_invoke_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hwport_id,
-				    u32 default_base_fqid,
-				    u32 default_hash_size);
+    u32 default_base_fqid,
+    u32 default_hash_size);
+
+/* fman_pcd_record_pending_port:
+ *   v1.1-A same-module helper. fman_port.c calls this from the
+ *   -ENOENT fall-through branch of fman_port_init() (i.e. when no
+ *   pre-netdev hook was installed at the moment the port probed) to
+ *   record (port_id, default_base_fqid, default_hash_size) on the
+ *   PCD's pending_ports list. ask later calls
+ *   fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() to replay the hook
+ *   for everything captured here. NOT exported (same TU as fman_port.c
+ *   from the kbuild merge into fsl_dpaa_fman.ko). Returns 0 on success,
+ *   -EINVAL if @pcd is NULL, -ENOMEM if the record cannot be allocated.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_record_pending_port(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hwport_id,
+				 u32 default_base_fqid,
+				 u32 default_hash_size);
 
 #endif /* __FMAN_PCD_INTERNAL_H */
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
index 079f1d3..33d82e2 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
@@ -1503,15 +1503,35 @@ int fman_port_init(struct fman_port *port)
 						     port->cfg->pcd_fqs_count);
 		if (err == 0) {
 			fman_port_use_kg_hash(port, true);
-		} else if (err == -ENOENT) {
-			err = keygen_port_hashing_init(keygen, port->port_id,
-						       port->cfg->pcd_base_fqid,
-						       port->cfg->pcd_fqs_count);
-			if (err)
-				return err;
+} else if (err == -ENOENT) {
+/*
+ * v1.1-A: record this port on the PCD's pending_ports
+ * list so a late-registering hook (ask_init() racing
+ * the fman_port platform-bus probe) can replay the
+ * install via fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports().
+ * Failure here is non-fatal -- the port simply will
+ * not be retroactively re-claimed; mainline RSS still
+ * applies. WARN-and-continue.
+ */
+{
+int rec = fman_pcd_record_pending_port(pcd_hook,
+port->port_id,
+port->cfg->pcd_base_fqid,
+port->cfg->pcd_fqs_count);
+if (rec && rec != -EINVAL)
+dev_warn(port->dev,
+ "fman_port: pending_port record failed: %d\n",
+ rec);
+}
 
-			fman_port_use_kg_hash(port, true);
-		} else {
+err = keygen_port_hashing_init(keygen, port->port_id,
+       port->cfg->pcd_base_fqid,
+       port->cfg->pcd_fqs_count);
+if (err)
+return err;
+
+fman_port_use_kg_hash(port, true);
+} else {
 			return err;
 		}
 	}
diff --git a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
index d0f1161..cfee242 100644
--- a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
+++ b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
@@ -115,10 +115,43 @@ typedef int (*fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t)(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
 					  void *priv);
 
 int fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
-				      fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t hook,
-				      void *priv);
+      fman_pcd_pre_netdev_hook_t hook,
+      void *priv);
 void fman_pcd_unregister_pre_netdev_hook(struct fman_pcd *pcd);
 
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() - retroactively invoke
+ * the registered pre-netdev hook for every fman_port that completed
+ * fman_port_init() BEFORE the hook was installed.
+ * @pcd: PCD handle.
+ *
+ * v1.1-A late-registration replay. Even though ask is built-in and
+ * its fs_initcall runs before dpaa_eth's device_initcall, async/parallel
+ * platform probing means individual fman_port platform devices may
+ * complete their probe ahead of ask_init(). Each such port is captured
+ * (port_id, default_base_fqid, default_hash_size) on the PCD's internal
+ * pending_ports list at the moment it falls through to mainline's
+ * keygen_port_hashing_init(). After ask has called
+ * fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook() it should immediately call this
+ * function to drain that list, invoking the freshly-registered hook
+ * for every captured port. Successfully-claimed entries (hook returns
+ * 0) are removed; -ENOENT entries stay queued for a future hook;
+ * fatal errors propagate (the failing entry is dropped to avoid retry
+ * loops).
+ *
+ * Acceptance signature: after the call, dmesg should show
+ *   "fman_pcd: install_now: claimed=N declined=M failed=K"
+ * with N matching the count of FMan ports ask is configured to own.
+ *
+ * Locking: takes pcd->lock briefly to splice the snapshot in/out;
+ * the hook runs OUTSIDE the lock and may sleep.
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success (including empty pending_ports list); negative
+ * errno propagated from the first fatal hook invocation; -EINVAL if
+ * @pcd is NULL; -ENOENT if no hook is currently registered.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports(struct fman_pcd *pcd);
+
 
 /*
  * OOT consumer entry points (PR14g-prep).
-- 
2.39.5

